      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is Olaplex No.3 a conditioner?",
            "content": "<p>No — it’s an at-home bond-repair treatment used before you shampoo. It reduces breakage and strengthens damaged hair by repairing the bonds inside the hair structure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I use Olaplex No.3?",
            "content": "<p>Apply to damp hair from roots to ends, leave it on for at least 10 minutes (longer for more damaged hair), then rinse, shampoo, and condition. Use it once or up to two to three times a week for damaged hair.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Who is Olaplex No.3 for?",
            "content": "<p>All hair types, especially hair with visible damage from coloring, bleaching, or heat. It’s also great for maintaining results between salon chemical services.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
